org.opendaylight.controller.networkconfig.neutron

Class NeutronSecurityRule

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.opendaylight.controller.configuration.ConfigurationObject
      • org.opendaylight.controller.networkconfig.neutron.NeutronSecurityRule
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class NeutronSecurityRule
extends ConfigurationObject
implements java.io.Serializable
    See OpenStack Network API v2.0 Reference for description of annotated attributes. The current fields are as follows:

    id uuid (String) UUID for the security group rule. security_rule_id uuid (String) The security group to associate rule. direction String Direction the VM traffic (ingress/egress). security_group_id The security group to associate rule with. protocol String IP Protocol (icmp, tcp, udp, etc). port_range_min Integer Port at start of range port_range_max Integer Port at end of range ethertype String ethertype in L2 packet (IPv4, IPv6, etc) remote_ip_prefix String (IP cidr) CIDR for address range. remote_group_id uuid-str Source security group to apply to rule. tenant_id uuid-str Owner of security rule. Admin only outside tenant.
